The book is a collection of unofficial fan predictions - it never
presents itself as true - nor was it something JKR planned to produce.
&quot;What will happen&quot; is really a news story expanded - with SPECULATION
about the books. While the USE of the characters are not public domain -
the stories and characters are a news story - much like a politician or
a movie star is.

Mugglenet stopped selling merchandise based on WB's contract with JKR -
which gave them the right to those profits.

While all fanfiction, based on the use of the characters, infringes - it
is non-commercial - not sold for profit - and most important - does not
represent itself as &quot;real&quot;(At least in the scheme of Harry Potter). This
new book would represent itself as an authority on the subject - which
is NOT TRUE - as well as being something that JKR has already stated
publicly that she would produce for the series.

AS far as the time line - there is no question that it belongs to JKR -
she wrote the books. THe timeline from Mugglenet is derived from the
books - they have no inside information to develop it otherwise.
